      "content": "i get the environment argument, but i've read some papers that suggest genetics actually play a bigger role in things like bone density or even how we process certain nutrients. if i'm working with a diverse group, wouldn't it be more efficient if i could at least look at the statistical trends that exist in certain ethnic populations? like, if certain groups are statistically more prone to higher muscle mass or higher oxidative capacity, shouldn't a specialized coach know that so they can tailor the intensity better for those specific bodies?",
